latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Our Patron of Art series has been celebrating prominent supporters of artistic movements throughout history since 1992. After 30 years we are bringing the series to an end with new writing instruments celebrating the British Queen Victoria and her husband Prince Albert. The Patron of Art Homage to Victoria Limited Edition 888 features a cap and barrel made of red lacquer and a solid gold overlay, inspired by her coronation outfit, while the Patron of Art Homage to Albert Limited Edition 888 pays tribute to Prince Albert and his work, with a solid gold overlay inspired by the iconic Crystal Palace exhibition centre.

#MontblancHighArtistry up close II Montblanc Artisan Atelier. Métiers d’art stone setting. Hamburg.

For over a century our Maison has developed different know-hows combining subtle variations and adjustments to traditional craftsmanship's with high precision technological tools. ​
​
These métiers d’arts mastery allows the Maison to offer absolutely unique pieces of craftmanship combining stone cutting unique technique with extra ordinary stone setting art, engraving and gold nib crafting, among others.​
​
These know-hows come to life into High Artistry pieces of fascinating beauty pushing the limits of excellency and telling a fragment of our Maison story.

#MontblancHaus, 2022. 
A place to celebrate writing. Now open.

Montblanc Haus was built to inspire writing, a destination that tells the story of Montblanc from its founding days to the present, of the women and men that craft Montblanc’s writing instruments and of those who have used them to share their imprint on humanity.

#InspireWriting

More than a century has passed between the maison’s first professional workshop in Hamburg’s Industrial Palace and the opening of the Montblanc Haus next to the Manufacture. Even as the buildings have changed, the quest for perfection remains a constant.

#MontblancHaus #InspireWriting

You put treasures in chests, jewels in safes, and even smartphones in cases.
And your precious writing instrument?

In our novel “BY” series, we spotlight supervising art director Stephan Gessler, the mastermind who, alongside production designer Adam Stockhausen, brought enchanting sets to life in the Maison’s “100 Years of Meisterstück” campaign film. Join us as he shares the inspiration and artistry behind translating Wes Anderson’s cinematic vision into reality.
